<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Name of restaurant</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 18.3738%;">
<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Location</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 33.7565%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;" align="center"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">Reason for recommendation</span></strong></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 32.0473%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal;" align="center"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">Other comments</span></strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody data-start="220" data-end="756">
<tr style="height: 68.7031px;" data-start="220" data-end="385">
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 15.81%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">The Junction</span></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 18.3738%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">Greyson Street, near the station</span></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 33.7565%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">Good for people who are especially keen on <strong>{fish} .</strong></span></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 32.0473%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">Quite expensive<br>The <strong>{roof}</strong> is a good place for a drink</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 85.9688px;" data-start="386" data-end="568">
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 15.81%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">Paloma</span></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 18.3738%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">In Bow Street next to the cinema</span></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 33.7565%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">{Spanish}</span></strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;"> food, good for sharing</span></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 32.0473%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">Staff are very friendly<br>Need to pay £50 deposit<br>A limited selection of <strong>{vegeterian}</strong> food on the menu</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 85.9688px;" data-start="569" data-end="756">
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 15.81%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">The <strong>{Audley}</strong></span></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 18.3738%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">At the top of a <strong>{hotel} </strong></span></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 33.7565%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">A famous chef<br>All the <strong>{reviews}</strong> are very good<br>Only uses <strong>{local} </strong> ingredients</span></p>
</td>
<td style="border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0.75pt; width: 32.0473%;">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;">Set lunch costs £9<strong> {30 | thirty}</strong> per person<br>Portions probably of <strong>{average} </strong>size</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>WOMAN:</strong> I’ve been meaning to ask you for some advice about restaurants. I need to book somewhere to celebrate my sister’s 30th birthday, and I liked the sound of that place you went to for your mum’s 50th.</p>\n<p><strong>MAN: </strong>The Junction. Yeah, I’d definitely recommend that for a special occasion. We had a great time there. Everyone really enjoyed it.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN:</strong> Where is it again? I can’t remember.</p>\n<p><strong>MAN:</strong> It is on Grayson Street only about a two walk from the station.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN:</strong> Oh that’s good I prefer not to have to drive anywhere but I don’t want to have to walk too far either.</p>\n<p><strong>MAN:</strong> Yes, the location’s perfect, but that’s not necessarily why I’d recommend it. The food’s amazing. If you like <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>fish</strong></span>, it’s probably the best restaurant in town for that. It’s always really fresh and there are lots of interesting dishes to choose from But all the food is good there.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN:</strong> Is it really expensive?</p>\n<p><strong>MAN: </strong>It’s certainly not cheap, but for a special occasion I think it’s fine. It’s got a great atmosphere and before dinner you can go up on the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>roof</strong></span> and have a drink. It’s really nice up there, but you need to book. It’s very popular as the views are spectacular.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN: </strong>Sounds good. So that’s definitely a possibility then. Is there anywhere else you can think of?</p>\n<p><strong>MAN:</strong> If you want somewhere a bit less formal, then you could try Paloma.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN: </strong>Where’s that? I haven’t heard of it.</p>\n<p><strong>MAN: </strong>No, it’s quite new. It’s only been open a few months, but it’s got a great reputation already. It’s in a really beautiful old building on Bow Street.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN: </strong>Oh, I think I know where you mean. Right beside the cinema.</p>\n<p><strong>MAN: </strong>Yes, that’s it. I’ve only been there a couple of times, but I was really impressed. The chef used to work at Don Felipe’s, apparently. I was really sorry when that closed down.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN: </strong>So is all the food they serve <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>Spanish</strong></span>, then?</p>\n<p><strong>MAN: </strong>Yeah. You can get lots of small dishes to share, which always works really well if you’re in a group.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN:</strong> Hmm. Worth thinking about.</p>\n<p><strong>MAN: </strong>Yeah. There’s a lively atmosphere and the waiters are really friendly. The only thing is that you need to pay a £50 deposit to book a table.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN:</strong> A lot of restaurants are doing that these days. I should have a look at the menu to check if there is a good choice of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>vegetarian</strong></span> dishes. A couple of my friends have stopped eating meat</p>\n<p><strong>MAN:</strong> Not sure I say the selection of those would be quite limited.</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Before you hear the rest of the conversation, you have some time to look at questions five to ten.</strong></span></p>\n<p><strong>MAN:</strong> I’ve just thought of another idea. Have you been to the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>Audley</strong></span>?</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN: </strong>No, don’t think I’ve heard of it. How’s it spelt?</p>\n<p><strong>MAN:</strong> A-U-D-L-E-Y. You must have heard of it. There’s been a lot about it in the press.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN:</strong> I don’t tend to pay much attention to that kind of thing. So where is it exactly?</p>\n<p><strong>MAN:</strong> It’s in that <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>hotel</strong></span> near Baxter Bridge, on the top floor.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN:</strong> Oh, the views would be incredible from up there.</p>\n<p><strong>MAN: </strong>Yeah, I’d love to go. I can’t think of the chef’s name, but she was a judge on that TV cookery show recently. And she’s written a couple of cookery books.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN: </strong>Oh, Angela Frayne.</p>\n<p><strong>MAN: </strong>That’s the one. Anyway, it had excellent <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>reviews</strong></span> from all the newspapers.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN:</strong> That would be a memorable place for a celebration.</p>\n<p><strong>MAN:</strong> Definitely.Obviously it’s worth going there just for the view, but the food is supposed to be really special.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN:</strong> She only likes cooking with <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>local</strong></span> products, doesn’t she?</p>\n<p><strong>MAN:</strong> Yes.Everything at the restaurant has to be sourced within a short distance, and absolutely nothing flown in from abroad.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN:</strong> I imagine it’s really expensive though.</p>\n<p><strong>MAN: </strong>Well, you could go for the set lunch.That’s quite reasonable for a top-class restaurant.<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>Thirty</strong></span> pounds a head.In the evening, I think it’d be more like fifty pounds.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN:</strong> At least that, I should think.But I’m sure everyone would enjoy it.It’s not the kind of place you leave feeling hungry though, is it? With tiny portions.</p>\n<p><strong>MAN:</strong> No, the reviews I’ve read didn’t mention that.I imagine they’d be <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>average</strong></span>.</p>\n<p><strong>WOMAN: </strong>Well, that’s all great.Thanks so much.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('449989af-8404-4229-aac0-eb22f7bbd718', 'ec953306-f0ba-4b9b-9940-2152cefdebb4', 'radio', 'Questions 31–34', '', '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "Its role is underestimated by parents."}, {"option_text": "It may shape the characteristics of adults."}, {"option_text": "Its importance decreases as children grow up."}, {"option_text": "It has more influence on personality than genetics."}], "question": "What point does the writer make about birth order in the third paragraph?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "Their parents treated them fairly."}, {"option_text": "They were treated harshly by their siblings."}, {"option_text": "Their perceptions of childhood may be inaccurate."}, {"option_text": "They have closer relations with their siblings as adults."}], "question": "What are we told about some of Claire Cartwright''s clients?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "Parents tend to repeat their own parents'' mistakes."}, {"option_text": "Favoured children are likely to make good leaders as adults."}, {"option_text": "Negative characteristics in children can become positive in adults."}, {"option_text": "Attention-seeking children are unlikely to please bosses in later life."}], "question": "What is the writer''s main point about siblings in the fifth paragraph?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "Many children have a favourite parent."}, {"option_text": "Parenting skills improve with later children."}, {"option_text": "Siblings are born with different personalities."}, {"option_text": "The family environment may change over time."}], "question": "Which of the following best summarises the writer''s argument in the sixth paragraph?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. What point does the writer make about birth order in the third paragraph? — {B. It may shape the characteristics of adults.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“It starts with birth order, which determines play roles… These are <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">roles that can stick for life</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả liệt kê các vai trò như “người lãnh đạo” (leader) hay “người hòa giải” (mediator) dựa trên thứ tự sinh và nhấn mạnh rằng những vai trò này có thể theo ta suốt đời (stick for life). Điều này đồng nghĩa với việc thứ tự sinh hình thành nên đặc điểm tính cách khi trưởng thành.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. What are we told about some of Claire Cartwright’s clients? — {C. Their perceptions of childhood may be inaccurate.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Clinical psychologist Claire Cartwright says she has clients who <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">believe, and it might not have been true</strong>, that they were treated differently from their siblings…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “might not have been true” (có thể đã không đúng như vậy) cho thấy niềm tin của các khách hàng về việc bị đối xử phân biệt trong quá khứ có thể không chính xác (inaccurate).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. What is the writer’s main point about siblings in the fifth paragraph? — {C. Negative characteristics in children can become positive in adults.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“On the other hand, the sibling who is <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">disruptive and annoying [Negative characteristics]</strong> as a child may be able to <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">reinterpret that role later</strong>, turning those attention-seeking characteristics into <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"218\">strengths like determination and leadership [Positive in adults]</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ý chính của đoạn này là những đứa trẻ từng có tính cách gây rối hoặc phiền phức (tiêu cực) có thể chuyển hóa những đặc tính đó thành thế mạnh như sự quyết tâm hoặc khả năng lãnh đạo (tích cực) khi lớn lên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2ece2f3c-57fe-4d7b-b9ab-b04bec12cb1f', 'af935e2f-33ab-4453-9d77-f453b5f73c94', 'matrix', 'Questions 19–21', '', '<p>Choose the correct business person, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>E</strong>, for each statement.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of people", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Employees should be kept informed about business developments and performance", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Work output increases when employees have a good balance between company and family responsibilities", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "It is critical to business success that all company members recognise that they matter", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Jennifer West", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Stephen Harper", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Margaret Mills", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Victor Davies", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "Hazel Gibbs", "categoryLetter": "E"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"1999\" data-end=\"2028\"><strong data-start=\"2002\" data-end=\"2028\">19. B (Stephen Harper)</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2030\" data-end=\"2066\"><strong data-start=\"2030\" data-end=\"2041\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn B, phần đầu đoạn.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2068\" data-end=\"2251\"><strong data-start=\"2068\" data-end=\"2082\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"2082\" data-end=\"2085\">“…every two weeks… they also get an update about the company, including who their new customers are, what successes they’ve had, and what challenges they are facing.”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2253\" data-end=\"2374\"><strong data-start=\"2253\" data-end=\"2268\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"2268\" data-end=\"2271\">Harper đảm bảo nhân viên được cập nhật thường xuyên về tình hình công ty → phù hợp với yêu cầu câu hỏi.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2381\" data-end=\"2409\"><strong data-start=\"2384\" data-end=\"2409\">20. D (Victor Davies)</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2411\" data-end=\"2465\"><strong data-start=\"2411\" data-end=\"2422\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn C, câu trích dẫn của Victor Davies.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2467\" data-end=\"2607\"><strong data-start=\"2467\" data-end=\"2481\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"2481\" data-end=\"2484\">“…maintain equilibrium between work and home, a policy which ultimately results in a more productive and stable workforce.”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2609\" data-end=\"2720\"><strong data-start=\"2609\" data-end=\"2624\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"2624\" data-end=\"2627\">Ông khẳng định cân bằng công việc – gia đình giúp tăng năng suất → đúng với nội dung câu hỏi.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2727\" data-end=\"2753\"><strong data-start=\"2730\" data-end=\"2753\">21. E (Hazel Gibbs)</strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2755\" data-end=\"2792\"><strong data-start=\"2755\" data-end=\"2766\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn D, phần giữa đoạn.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2794\" data-end=\"2905\"><strong data-start=\"2794\" data-end=\"2808\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><br data-start=\"2808\" data-end=\"2811\">“…she works hard to ensure that everyone, from managers to workers, realizes that they count.”</p>\n<p data-start=\"2907\" data-end=\"3033\"><strong data-start=\"2907\" data-end=\"2922\">Giải thích:</strong><br data-start=\"2922\" data-end=\"2925\">Gibbs nhấn mạnh tất cả nhân viên đều quan trọng → điều này rất cần thiết cho sự thành công của doanh nghiệp.</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('07846d4e-47f0-4faa-ae70-ae6d1902ca52', '5e03fc9f-f2d7-46f6-932c-e7dae48bfc20', 'radio', 'Question 11-16', NULL, '<p data-start="79" data-end="120">Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</p>', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. it lasts longer in the ground."}, {"content": "B. it is practised by more people."}, {"content": "C. it can be repaired more easily."}], "question": "Heather says pottery differs from other art forms because", "explanation": "Ví dụ cho việc giải thích tại đây."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. the clay it was made with."}, {"content": "B. the marks that are on it."}, {"content": "C. the basic shape of it."}], "question": "Archaeologists sometimes identify the use of ancient pottery from"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. create an item that looks very old."}, {"content": "B. find something that they are good at."}, {"content": "C. make something that will outlive them."}], "question": "Some people join Heather’s pottery class because they want to"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. its calming effect"}, {"content": "B. its messy nature"}, {"content": "C. its physical benefits"}], "question": "What does Heather value most about being a potter?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. bring friends to join courses."}, {"content": "B. have never made a pot before."}, {"content": "C. try to learn techniques too quickly."}], "question": "Most of the visitors to Edelman Pottery"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. put on their aprons."}, {"content": "B. change their clothes."}, {"content": "C. take off their jewellery."}], "question": "Heather reminds her visitors that they should"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>(Questions 11–16)</strong></span></p>\n<p><strong>HEATHER McCALLUM:</strong> Hello and welcome. My name’s Heather McCallum and I’m one of the potters who work here at Edelman Pottery. Before we go into the workshop, I just want to say a bit about the craft of pottery. Then we’ll have a look at the equipment and you can try making a pot of your own.</p>\n<p>Like many people, I’m sure you know that pottery as an art form is tens of thousands of years old. And we know this because it stands the test of time. Things like baskets and pictures don’t survive in the earth in the same way that pots do. And even if ancient pots are found in small pieces, they still provide a lot of information about the past. There’s no doubt that pottery has given archaeologists a fascinating insight into how ancient humans lived.</p>\n<p>The shape of an artefact may have been lost, but archaeologists can tell whether the pots were for, say, storage or cooking by examining the impressions on the clay, the scratches from tools. And the clay itself can reveal where the pots came from.</p>\n<p>When I ask people why they want to take a pottery class with me, they sometimes talk about these things. Like our ancestors, they hope that something they create will also last longer than they do. That their work, whether it is good or not, might say something about humanity many years after their death.</p>\n<p>Of course, you will all have your own reasons for coming here. As far as I’m concerned, what I love most is the concentration you need to make a good pot. That focus takes you away from the stresses of everyday life. If you’re elderly, it’s also good exercise for hands and wrists and helps with arthritis. And of course, it’s a fun activity for children, because it’s so messy.</p>\n<p>Here at Edelman Pottery, we show you some of the basic pottery techniques so that you can use these to create whatever you wish. A gift for a friend, perhaps. Like nearly everyone who comes here, I’m sure this is the first time you will have tried the art, so we’ll keep things simple today.</p>\n<p>Now, before we move on, can I just say a word about what you’re wearing? As we said in our email, please remove any watches, necklaces, etc., and put them somewhere safe. If you have long hair, do tie it back now. We’ll provide aprons later, but I trust your clothes are old but comfortable, not your favourite T-shirt or jeans.</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Phần 2 (Questions 17–20)</strong></span><br> </p>\n<p><strong>HEATHER McCALLUM: </strong>So now we’re in the workshop. Have a look around. There’s a lot going on. To make pottery that will last, you need a potter’s wheel, a kiln, which is basically a very hot oven where you fire the pottery, and some tools.</p>\n<p>So first, the kiln. If you look over in the far corner, you’ll see one of ours. Since their invention, kilns have changed very little, though in the past 20 years a lot of progress has been made in temperature control. Basically, a kiln removes the water from clay at temperatures of around 1,000 degrees Celsius. This allows anything you’ve made to set permanently in shape. It’s a pretty ugly, heavy object that’s hard to keep in a house or flat, so most people don’t have one.</p>\n<p>You may think, can’t I use my oven? Well, that’s possible, but domestic ovens don’t really get hot enough, and eventually the clay will crack and fall apart. Some people fire pottery in a fire pit outside, but bear in mind that can be dangerous. You also need to know about safety procedures for kilns as they release toxic compounds into the air.</p>\n<p>Every potter needs a potter’s wheel. This machine is used to shape the clay into an object with circular walls or sides, such as a bowl. Its invention revolutionised the pottery industry, allowing multiple items to be produced in a day.</p>\n<p>Lastly, there are a number of different tools that potters use, depending on what they want to make. When you start, your hands can make all kinds of shapes and curves without relying on a sculpting tool. However, there are some basic tools that you will need to handle the clay on the wheel. Some look very strange and have even odder names that you may find hard to remember. Rather than go through them all now, I’ll just name a few tools as we go along. We can provide these, and I wouldn’t recommend spending money on them yet.</p>\n<p>So, let’s try making a pot of your own.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fefb8e3c-33a2-46fb-858b-d6138756525f', '1bf722d0-0787-401d-b345-198af6f4bb80', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–6', '<p data-path-to-node="5">Complete the form below.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="6">Write <strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="6">ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9592%; height: 2px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 2px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 99.8776%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: left;" data-path-to-node="7,0"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Guitar Group</strong></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="7,1,0,0">Coordinator: Gary {Mathieson}</p>
<p data-path-to-node="7,1,1,0">Level: {beginners}</p>
<p data-path-to-node="7,1,2,0">Place: the {college}</p>
<p data-path-to-node="7,1,3,0">{New} Street</p>
<p data-path-to-node="7,1,4,0">First floor, Room T347</p>
<p data-path-to-node="7,1,5,0">Time: Thursday morning at {11|eleven}</p>
<p data-path-to-node="7,1,6,0">Recommended website: ''The perfect {instrument}''</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p data-path-to-node="6"> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('77c13a6e-a046-4f64-a2ba-03efe3d153ae', '5e03fc9f-f2d7-46f6-932c-e7dae48bfc20', 'checkbox', 'Questions 19 - 20', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, A–E.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>points does Heather make about a potter''s tools?</p>', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A. Some are hard to hold.", "correct": false}, {"option": "B. Some are worth buying.", "correct": true}, {"option": "C. Some are essential items.", "correct": false}, {"option": "D. Some have memorable names.", "correct": true}, {"option": "E. Some are available for use by participants.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9148a573-dd92-4e8a-9f12-9262c9eb1fdf', 'a639ec40-8b6b-46e1-bd4c-6533903d938e', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21-22 ', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p><strong>21-22</strong> Which <strong>TWO </strong>things do the students both believe are responsible for the increase in<br>loneliness?</p>', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A social media", "correct": false}, {"option": "B smaller nuclear families", "correct": false}, {"option": "C urban design", "correct": true}, {"option": "D longer lifespans", "correct": false}, {"option": "E a mobile workforce", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>(Questions 21–26)</strong></span></p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>Shall we go through the notes we’ve made from our research into loneliness now, Dev?</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>OK, Tamara.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV:</strong> It’s been a real eye-opener.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV:</strong> I had no idea that loneliness has been increasing steadily for the last 20 years.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> I know.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> And it’s the same all over the world.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> The downside of a modern lifestyle, I guess.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV:</strong> Did you come to any conclusions about what the reasons for the increase are?</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> Well, I’d assumed it was mainly an issue for the elderly, but in fact it’s something which affects young people just as much.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>So nothing really to do with longer lifespans.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>What about social media?</p>\n<p><strong>DEV:</strong> In my case, far from making me feel isolated, it actually does the opposite.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> It definitely does more good than harm.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>I’d say loneliness has a lot to do with the way cities are designed.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>People living in high-rise flats with not much opportunity to speak to their neighbours.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>I think you’re right.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> Another possible reason is that people are having fewer children and don’t live in large extended family groups.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV:</strong> But in this country, anyway, that all changed decades ago.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV:</strong> And yet loneliness is a more recent problem.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> I suppose so.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>A more plausible explanation is that people are having to move around for work and often end up living miles away from their family and friends.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>That’s true.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> Looking at the studies on health risks and loneliness, there are claims that loneliness has as much impact as smoking 15 cigarettes a day.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>Or similar to the risks caused by obesity.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>But I’m not sure there’s enough evidence for some of these claims.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>Well, what about that one in Finland which showed that loneliness increased the risk of cancer by about 10%?</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>And those findings have been supported by other studies too.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>You’re right about that one.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV:</strong> I was actually thinking of the studies on dementia.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>Some found no association between loneliness and dementia and others found the opposite.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> Not exactly reliable then.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>There’s been a lot of research on cardiovascular disease and whether loneliness contributes to that.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV:</strong> Yes.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV:</strong> I read that it was hard to reach a judgement as the definition of loneliness varied quite a lot and the responses from participants were too subjective.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>But there’s no doubt that loneliness contributes to a weakened immune system.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>Unquestionably.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>The data on that is sound.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>What did you think about the evolutionary theory of loneliness?</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>Well, I thought the idea that loneliness evolved because it motivated people to be with other people quite convincing.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> Survival often depended on group cooperation.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>But I don’t think there’s enough evidence to claim that there must be a group of neurons in our brains which influence social behaviour by making us feel bad when we’re alone.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>There are a few studies which support the theory but not conclusively enough.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>More evidence is needed.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>And anyway, this theory’s not really useful when it comes to solving the problem of loneliness today.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>True. </p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>(Questions 27–30)</strong></span></p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>Should we look at the relationship between loneliness and mental health now?</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>OK.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>So loneliness and depression are clearly related and that’s been recognised by various governments around the world.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> But unlike depression, loneliness has no recognised clinical form.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>There’s no available diagnosis or effective treatment and that’s not likely to change.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> I don’t think so either.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>I was thinking we should start our presentation with an example from our own experience.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> I’d like to talk about how lonely I was when I started university, being away from home for the first time and all that.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>Good idea.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>Everyone will be able to relate to that, although a lot of students were probably too embarrassed to admit to it.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>Yeah.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>We could discuss ways of dealing with loneliness as well, like just talking to strangers.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>Loads of studies have shown that interactions with shop assistants and bar staff make people feel more optimistic and relaxed.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> I don’t know about that, but it must make people feel more connected with their community.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>True.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>Although you need to be a certain kind of person to be able to just strike up a conversation.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>Good point.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>We should say something about solitude and how being alone and being lonely aren’t the same thing.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA:</strong> It’s strange the way some people can’t stand being by themselves while others love it.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>Yeah, the research shows a certain amount of solitude is beneficial for well-being, which I appreciate, but being alone isn’t something I actually like.</p>\n<p><strong>DEV: </strong>I’d never choose to go on holiday alone, for example.</p>\n<p><strong>TAMARA: </strong>Me neither.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('234dd2f4-3546-4243-ba77-280a480184d0', 'a639ec40-8b6b-46e1-bd4c-6533903d938e', 'radio', 'Questions 23-24', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p><strong>23-24</strong> Which <strong>TWO </strong>health risks associated with loneliness do the students agree are based<br />
on solid evidence</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. doubt that there will ever be a medical cure for loneliness."}, {"content": "B. claim that the link between loneliness and mental health is overstated."}, {"content": "C. express frustration that loneliness is not taken more seriously."}], "question": "27 When comparing loneliness to depression, the students"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. to explain how difficult loneliness can be"}, {"content": "B. to highlight a situation that most students will recognise"}, {"content": "C. to emphasise that feeling lonely is more common for men than women"}], "question": "28 Why do the students decide to start their presentation with an example from their own experience?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. it creates a sense of belonging."}, {"content": "B. it builds self-confidence."}, {"content": "C. it makes people feel more positive."}], "question": "29 The students agree that talking to strangers is a good strategy for dealing with loneliness because"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. similar to loneliness."}, {"content": "B. necessary for mental health"}, {"content": "C. an enjoyable experience."}], "question": "30 The students find it difficult to understand why solitude is considered to be"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('351242f0-7d5b-4255-8cba-54868bb59b87', 'a639ec40-8b6b-46e1-bd4c-6533903d938e', 'checkbox', 'Questions 25-26', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers</p>
<p><strong>25-26</strong> Which <strong>TWO </strong>opinions do both the students express about the evolutionary theory of<br />
loneliness?.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A. It has little practical relevance", "correct": true}, {"option": "B. It needs further investigation.", "correct": false}, {"option": "C. It is misleading.", "correct": true}, {"option": "D. It should be more widely accepted.", "correct": false}, {"option": "E. It is difficult to understand.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('be61f8c7-43da-4b94-92c8-cb0a1070efa6', 'a639ec40-8b6b-46e1-bd4c-6533903d938e', 'radio', 'Questions 27–30', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;" data-start="127" data-end="159"><strong>Loneliness and mental health</strong></h3>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. doubt that there will ever be a medical cure for loneliness."}, {"content": "B. claim that the link between loneliness and mental health is overstated."}, {"content": "C. express frustration that loneliness is not taken more seriously."}], "question": "When comparing loneliness to depression, the students"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. to explain how difficult loneliness can be"}, {"content": "B. to highlight a situation that most students will recognise"}, {"content": "C. to emphasise that feeling lonely is more common for men than women"}], "question": "Why do the students decide to start their presentation with an example from their own experience?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. it creates a sense of belonging."}, {"content": "B. it builds self-confidence."}, {"content": "C. it makes people feel more positive."}], "question": "The students agree that talking to strangers is a good strategy for dealing with loneliness because"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. similar to loneliness."}, {"content": "B. necessary for mental health"}, {"content": "C. an enjoyable experience."}], "question": "The students find it difficult to understand why solitude is considered to be"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c5decbf2-ee70-485e-8b0b-4458b0641cac', 'dfe8748e-12ba-45d3-b622-91e5f3d4233d', 'checkbox', 'Questions 27 and 28', '', '<p data-start="1506" data-end="1534">Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>E</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="1536" data-end="1620">Which <strong>TWO </strong>things does Stella say students need to do for a successful interview?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "A. Guide the way in which the interview progresses"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B. Prepare the questions well in advance"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C. Check the recording equipment is working"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D. explain fully the purpose of the interview"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E. give a personal opinion on the topics which are covered"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f5cb96fa-edf7-40b4-8c40-4672ff5627bb', 'd6e42265-c2dc-4080-bab0-9b4e279a6111', 'fillup', 'Question 31-40', '<p style="text-align: left;" data-start="53" data-end="80">Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;" data-start="53" data-end="80"><strong data-start="53" data-end="80">Reclaiming urban rivers</strong></h3>
<p data-start="82" data-end="107"><strong data-start="82" data-end="107">Historical background</strong></p>
<ul data-start="108" data-end="484">
<li data-start="108" data-end="156">
<p data-start="110" data-end="156">Nearly all major cities were built on a river.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="157" data-end="245">
<p data-start="159" data-end="245">Rivers were traditionally used by city dwellers for transport, fishing and recreation.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="246" data-end="412">
<p data-start="248" data-end="307">Industrial development and rising populations later led to:</p>
<ul data-start="310" data-end="412">
<li data-start="310" data-end="367">
<p data-start="312" data-end="367">more sewage from houses being discharged into the river</p>
</li>
<li data-start="370" data-end="412">
<p data-start="372" data-end="412">pollution from <strong data-start="387" data-end="393">{factories}</strong> at the river bank.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="413" data-end="484">
<p data-start="415" data-end="484">In 1957, the River Thames in London was declared biologically {dead}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="486" data-end="509"><strong data-start="486" data-end="509">Recent improvements</strong></p>
<ul data-start="510" data-end="805">
<li data-start="510" data-end="571">
<p data-start="512" data-end="571">Seals and even a <strong data-start="529" data-end="535">{whale}</strong> have been seen in the River Thames.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="573" data-end="636">
<p data-start="575" data-end="636">Riverside warehouses are converted to restaurants and {apartments}</p>
</li>
<li data-start="638" data-end="733">
<p data-start="640" data-end="675">In Los Angeles, there are plans to:</p>
<ul data-start="678" data-end="733">
<li data-start="678" data-end="704">
<p data-start="680" data-end="704">build a riverside <strong data-start="698" data-end="704">{park}</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="707" data-end="733">
<p data-start="709" data-end="733">display {art}projects.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="735" data-end="805">
<p data-start="737" data-end="805">In Paris, <strong data-start="747" data-end="753">{beaches}</strong> are created on the sites of the river every summer.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="807" data-end="834"><strong data-start="807" data-end="834">Transport possibilities</strong></p>
<ul data-start="835" data-end="1129">
<li data-start="835" data-end="914">
<p data-start="837" data-end="914">Over 2 billion passengers already travel by <strong data-start="881" data-end="887">{ferry}</strong> in cities round the world.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="915" data-end="1002">
<p data-start="917" data-end="1002">Changes in shopping habits mean the number of deliveries that are made is increasing.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1003" data-end="1129">
<p data-start="1005" data-end="1129">Instead of road transport, goods could be transported by large freight barges and electric <strong data-start="1096" data-end="1102">{bikes}</strong>, or, in future, by <strong data-start="1122" data-end="1128">{drone}</strong>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>(Questions 31–40)<br /> </p>\n<p>SPEAKER: It&#8217;s quite hard to think of a city that doesn&#8217;t have a big river running through it. If you think about the major cities in the world, Shanghai, New York, Mumbai, London, they&#8217;re nearly all built on rivers. When these cities were established hundreds or even thousands of years ago, the rivers were a big part of people&#8217;s lives.</p>\n<p>In sixteenth-century London, the quickest way to get from one part of the city to another was by river. But people also used the river for fishing, as the water then was relatively clean, and they would also go on boat trips up and down the river just for pleasure, as a relaxing escape from the noise and bustle of the city streets.</p>\n<p>But as industries developed and populations increased, city rivers suffered. The rising number of people meant there was a huge increase in the amount of sewage discharged into the rivers. Rivers had always been used for this purpose, but when the number of inhabitants was so small, that wasn&#8217;t such a problem. However, as cities grew to over a million inhabitants, the impact on the rivers became more serious. In addition, other types of pollution increased as factories were built beside the river and discharged their waste materials into the water. This got worse over time. As recently as 1957, scientists at London&#8217;s Natural History Museum declared that the River Thames was dead in biological terms, as the water was too filthy to support any kind of life.</p>\n<p>But in recent years, as rivers lost their industrial function, cities have begun to recognise their true value and to take steps to clean them up. For example, the River Thames is now cleaner than it&#8217;s been for 150 years. These days, you can see seals swimming in the water, and recently people had to try to rescue a whale, which had got lost and swum up the river from the sea by mistake. Unfortunately, they didn&#8217;t succeed, but the problem was disorientation rather than the quality of the water.</p>\n<p>Then, all around the world, riverside areas are now seen as prime sites for development. Warehouses that were once used for storing goods are now being converted into expensive restaurants and also into apartments with river views, which are in great demand and sell for astronomical prices.</p>\n<p>In Los Angeles, on the west coast of the USA, an architect has plans to revitalise the banks of the river and to make a park there, which can provide facilities for sports as well as a natural environment for relaxing in. It&#8217;s also hoped that the riverside can be used for other purposes. It&#8217;s been proposed that facilities could be provided for displaying projects related to various kinds of art that have been produced by local people, for example.</p>\n<p>In the city of Paris, during the summer months of July and August, all the traffic is banned from the roads by the sides of the river, and the banks are transformed into beaches where people can relax in deck chairs under potted palm trees, sunbathe, or buy a drink or a snack while enjoying the view.</p>\n<p>But to make the most of our rivers in our increasingly crowded cities, we need to allow them to regain their original purpose and be used as a means of transport, reclaiming our streets from cars and lorries. To do this, we&#8217;ll have to shift more traffic back to the river, but this time cleanly and silently, making the most of modern technology.</p>\n<p>Already, more than two billion passengers use the ferry to travel in cities around the world, like Istanbul, San Francisco, and New York, and these numbers are set to rise further. Admittedly, it&#8217;s not a fast way of travelling, but neither is a car when it&#8217;s stuck in traffic.</p>\n<p>Of course, passenger traffic on roads might decrease as more people start working from home, but another recent development, the huge rise in online shopping, has meant that another form of urban traffic just keeps on growing, and that&#8217;s deliveries. Trucks and vans in the city pollute and double-park while dropping off parcels. Imagine using the immense capacity of shipping to take these trucks off the road. One freight barge can replace 44 large trucks, uses far less energy, and causes less pollution. When the barge docks at the riverside, the parcels could be taken the last few kilometres to their final destination on cargo bikes, electric ones of course. This is already happening in the Dutch city of Amsterdam, and in future, the final stage could even be carried out by drone, although at present, this isn&#8217;t allowed. Wouldn&#8217;t it be great to unblock our city centres in this way? Looking further ahead&#8230;</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bcd85c82-e18c-4b9c-b850-349904d5abc8', 'dfe8748e-12ba-45d3-b622-91e5f3d4233d', 'radio', 'Questions 21–22', '', '<p data-start="32" data-end="73">Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B </strong>or <strong>C</strong>.</p>
<h4 data-start="75" data-end="107">Field trip to Bolton Island</h4>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. because it is geologically unique"}, {"option_text": "B. because its easy accessible"}, {"option_text": "C. because large numbers of rare animals frequent it"}], "question": "Why were Mark and Stella attracted to Bolton Island for their field trip?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. the natural lagoon"}, {"option_text": "B. its fertile soil"}, {"option_text": "C. rock formation"}], "question": "Which aspect of Bolton Island’s physical geography did Mark and Stella focus on?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. getting useful information from the local residents"}, {"option_text": "B. recognising which features were man-made"}, {"option_text": "C. finding official data about the island"}], "question": "Which problem did Mark and Stella have in studying Bolton Island’s physical geography?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. reading previous field trip reports"}, {"option_text": "B. drawing up a detailed schedule for their trip"}, {"option_text": "C. doing online research"}], "question": "What preparation was most useful for Mark and Stella’s trip?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7173d60f-a0fc-4682-a632-fb333795fc91', '21ca61c7-0472-4687-8c42-9a7b1647085d', 'matrix', 'Question 11-16', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A-H</strong>, next to questions <strong>11-16.</strong></p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="data:image/png;base64," width="460" height="419" loading="lazy"></p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Toilet block", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Shower block", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Tent site", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Cabins", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Barbecue area", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Bike trail", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear the organizer of a family camp talking to a group of people who will be staying at a campsite. First you have some time to look at questions 11 to 16 on page three. Now listen carefully and answer questions 11 to sixteen.</p>\n<p>Hello everyone and welcome to this orientation session prior to our camp next week. Thank you for coming along to find out what you and your children will be doing on this year’s camp. To start off with, let’s tell you a bit about the campsite itself so that you’ll be able to find your way around once you get there.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Xin chào tất cả mọi người và chào mừng đến với buổi định hướng này trước khi trại của chúng ta diễn ra vào tuần tới. Cảm ơn các bạn đã đến để tìm hiểu về những gì bạn và con cái bạn sẽ làm trong kỳ trại năm nay. Để bắt đầu, hãy để tôi kể cho bạn một chút về khu cắm trại để bạn có thể tìm đường khi đến nơi.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Firstly, we’ll be arriving by bus into the car park which, if you look at the plan you have in front of you, you’ll see at the top of the picture on the left hand side. Now, if you cross the road from the car park, the first building you’ll come to is the <strong>(11) toilet block (A)</strong>. It’s been recently upgraded, so it’s very nice and clean in there now with plenty of facilities. And built onto that, so this is across the road from the community hall, is the new <strong>(12) shower block (C)</strong>. The hot water does run out occasionally, but usually there’s enough to cope with a group your size.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Đầu tiên, chúng ta sẽ đến bằng xe buýt vào <strong>bãi đậu xe</strong> mà, nếu bạn nhìn vào sơ đồ bạn có trước mặt, bạn sẽ thấy ở phía trên bên trái của bức tranh. Bây giờ, nếu bạn băng qua đường từ bãi đậu xe, tòa nhà đầu tiên bạn sẽ đến là <strong>(11) khu vệ sinh (A)</strong>. Nó đã được nâng cấp gần đây, vì vậy nó rất đẹp và sạch sẽ với đầy đủ tiện nghi. Và được xây dựng liền kề với nó, đối diện qua đường từ hội trường cộng đồng, là <strong>(12) khu tắm vòi sen (C)</strong> mới. Nước nóng thỉnh thoảng có hết, nhưng thường thì có đủ để phục vụ một nhóm có quy mô như nhóm của bạn.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>If you now move to the bottom left of your map, among the pine trees, there is a special flat site set up for pitching tents, with power points and outdoor taps for water. This is the <strong>(13) Tent site (G)</strong>. Now let’s go back and move along the top of your map. There’s another area of Pine Forest and then over on the far right hand side there’s a block of small <strong>(14) cabins (D)</strong>. Note that this is different from the main accommodation block which doesn’t appear on this map but is further over again to the right.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Nếu bạn di chuyển xuống phía dưới bên trái của bản đồ, giữa những cây thông, có một khu đất bằng phẳng đặc biệt được thiết lập để dựng lều, có ổ cắm điện và vòi nước ngoài trời. Đây là <strong>(13) khu cắm lều (G)</strong>. Bây giờ chúng ta hãy quay lại và di chuyển dọc theo phía trên của bản đồ. Có một khu rừng thông khác và sau đó ở phía ngoài cùng bên phải có một khối <strong>(14) cabin nhỏ (D)</strong>. Lưu ý rằng điều này khác với khu nhà ở chính (main accommodation block) không xuất hiện trên bản đồ này mà nằm xa hơn nữa về bên phải.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Now let’s look down from there over the road, so we’re moving clockwise round your map. Okay, in this next block beside the flower beds, we have a lovely place for barbecues where <strong>(15) you can cook in the open air (F)</strong>. What else to tell you about? Um, below the flower bed and across Lakeside Drive, you’ll see a trail for <strong>(16) mountain biking (H)</strong> which is always a popular activity. Moving on now in the middle of the campsite, you’ll see the lake where you can canoe, and above that again, the community hall. So that completes your introduction to the campsite. I hope you found that useful.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Bây giờ chúng ta hãy nhìn xuống từ đó qua đường, tức là chúng ta đang di chuyển theo chiều kim đồng hồ quanh bản đồ của bạn. Được rồi, trong khu vực tiếp theo bên cạnh các luống hoa, chúng ta có một nơi tuyệt vời để nướng thịt ngoài trời, nơi <strong>(15) bạn có thể nấu ăn ngoài trời (F)</strong>. Còn gì nữa để nói với các bạn? Ừm, bên dưới luống hoa và băng qua đường Lakeside Drive, bạn sẽ thấy một con đường mòn dành cho <strong>(16) đạp xe leo núi (H)</strong>, đây luôn là một hoạt động phổ biến. Tiếp theo, ở giữa khu cắm trại, bạn sẽ thấy hồ nơi bạn có thể chèo thuyền canoe, và phía trên đó là hội trường cộng đồng. Vậy là hoàn thành phần giới thiệu của tôi về khu cắm trại. Tôi hy vọng bạn thấy nó hữu ích.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the talk, you have some time to look at questions 17 to 20 on page four. Now listen and answer questions 17 to twenty.</p>\n<p>Now let’s think about what you need to bring with you. I’m sure you’re all wondering what you need to pack. The lake is a bit cold for swimming at this time of year, so you can leave your togs out of the suitcase. While we’re on the subject of weather too, usually I recommend that campers bring sunscreen with them, but I guess now that we’re into April, that too can be left behind. Ah, let me think. Some campers like a torch, but actually the days are still so long that it’s light outside till quite late, and the blocks all have outside lighting now, so I’d say that a pair of <strong>(17) earplugs (A)</strong> are more useful, as in my experience a lot of talking goes on after lights out. But in April, if it’s wet, it can get muddy around the campsite, so to bring <strong>(18) boots (E)</strong> isn’t a bad idea.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Bây giờ chúng ta hãy nghĩ về những gì bạn cần mang theo. Tôi chắc chắn tất cả các bạn đang tự hỏi mình cần đóng gói những gì. Hồ hơi lạnh để bơi vào thời điểm này trong năm, vì vậy bạn có thể bỏ đồ bơi ra khỏi vali. Về chủ đề thời tiết, thông thường tôi khuyên những người cắm trại mang theo kem chống nắng, nhưng tôi đoán bây giờ đã là tháng Tư rồi, nên thứ đó cũng có thể để lại. À, để tôi nghĩ xem. Một số người cắm trại thích mang theo đèn pin, nhưng thực ra ngày vẫn còn dài nên trời sáng khá muộn, và các khu nhà đều có đèn chiếu sáng bên ngoài rồi, vì vậy tôi nghĩ một cặp <strong>(17) nút bịt tai (A)</strong> sẽ hữu ích hơn, vì theo kinh nghiệm của tôi, rất nhiều cuộc trò chuyện diễn ra sau khi tắt đèn. Nhưng vào tháng Tư, nếu trời mưa, khu cắm trại có thể bị lầy lội, vì vậy mang theo <strong>(18) ủng (E)</strong> cũng không phải là ý tồi.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Finally, can you all please prepare something for the final night concert? Bring your musical instruments or whatever else you need. You can’t have a camp without a good <strong>sing along (D)</strong>. That’s our favourite activity. Maybe you could recite a poem (C) or act out a skit (A) or charades for us, if you’re brave enough to try that, or failing that, perhaps you can tell a funny story (E) or a joke. But actually, people much prefer to see some good <strong>(19) dancing (B)</strong>. <strong>(20)</strong> I’ll look forward to seeing you all perform next week.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Cuối cùng, tất cả các bạn vui lòng chuẩn bị một tiết mục nào đó cho buổi hòa nhạc đêm cuối cùng nhé? Hãy mang theo nhạc cụ hoặc bất cứ thứ gì bạn cần. Bạn không thể cắm trại mà thiếu một buổi <strong>(D) hát tập thể</strong> thật hay. Đó là hoạt động yêu thích của chúng tôi. Có lẽ bạn có thể đọc một bài thơ (C) hoặc diễn một vở kịch ngắn (A) hoặc trò chơi đố chữ cho chúng tôi, nếu bạn đủ dũng cảm để thử, hoặc nếu không được, có lẽ bạn có thể kể một câu chuyện cười hoặc một câu chuyện vui (E). Nhưng thực tế, mọi người thích xem một số màn <strong>(19) nhảy múa (B)</strong> hay hơn nhiều. <strong>(20)</strong> Tôi rất mong được thấy tất cả các bạn biểu diễn vào tuần tới.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 2. You now have half a minute to check your answers. Now turn to Section 3 on page five.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c34392b2-c112-44fd-8e59-448698f2b3de', '21ca61c7-0472-4687-8c42-9a7b1647085d', 'checkbox', 'Questions 17–18', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>items is it recommended that campers bring?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A earplugs", "correct": true}, {"option": "B sunscreen", "correct": false}, {"option": "C swimming toy", "correct": false}, {"option": "D torch", "correct": false}, {"option": "E boots", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('67cacceb-7c58-4494-8284-9705a5a61901', 'caad1aff-820d-41ab-b54b-c27f27580c0c', 'matrix', 'Questions 14–20', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 2 has eight paragraphs, <strong>A-H.</strong></p>
<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "A description of how a test showed some evidence to be fake", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Reasons why scientists may be unwilling to admit that they play", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "The result of a trick going wrong", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "The similarity between a skill used in play and one used in science", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "How a group of scientists stopped a colleague misusing their results", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Some examples of the playful nature of scientific language", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "An example of an everyday object put to a scientific use", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>14. A description of how a test showed some evidence to be fake</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: E</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “But in 1977, Helen Michel and Frank Asaro… showed that the <strong>copper and zinc used in the plate were of a higher quality than would have been available in the 1500s</strong>. They concluded that Drake’s plate was most likely crafted much closer to the time when it was first brought to light.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc phân tích chất liệu (đồng và kẽm) đã chứng minh tấm bảng là giả mạo (fake).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>15. Reasons why scientists may be unwilling to admit that they play</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: A</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) “…perhaps because scientists take it for granted, or because <strong>they are a little self-conscious about it and therefore try to hide it</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc cảm thấy bối rối/ngượng ngùng (self-conscious) là lý do họ che giấu/ngại thừa nhận.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>16. The result of a trick going wrong</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: F</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “Some of Bolton’s friends decided to play a joke on him, but <strong>things misfired</strong> after Bolton went public and announced that the relic was authentic <strong>before he could be told about the joke</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Trò đùa bị phản tác dụng (misfired) khi nạn nhân công bố thông tin trước khi biết đó là trò đùa.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>17. The similarity between a skill used in play and one used in science</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: B</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “Guessing the solution of a scientific problem has <strong>many similarities to completing a jigsaw puzzle</strong>… The best scientists are those who make the best guesses.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Kỹ năng đoán (guessing) trong giải đố (play) giống với việc giải quyết vấn đề khoa học.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>18. How a group of scientists stopped a colleague misusing their results</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: G</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “Lewis decided to set a trap for the co-worker… [but] <strong>this stopped him temporarily from taking our data and interpreting it before making sure that it was right</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Họ dùng một dữ liệu giả (fake NMR spectrum) để bẫy đồng nghiệp và ngăn anh ta công bố dữ liệu sai.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>19. Some examples of the playful nature of scientific language</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: D</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “Take, for example, the <strong>funny names</strong> that scientists have given to various chemical substances: <strong>tristane, windowpane, penguinone or megaphone</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các tên hài hước của hóa chất là ví dụ về sự vui đùa trong ngôn ngữ khoa học.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>20. An example of an everyday object put to a scientific use</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: C</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “The apparatus put together by Robert Millikan and Harvey Fletcher to measure the charge of the electron, which involved a <strong>perfume atomiser bought at a local pharmacy</strong>, is a classic example of such inspired tinkering.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bình xịt nước hoa (perfume atomiser) là một vật dụng hàng ngày được dùng trong thí nghiệm.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('75093230-7ae6-4b11-970b-97aaded070fa', 'caad1aff-820d-41ab-b54b-c27f27580c0c', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21–22', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> of the following reasons are given as possible explanations of scientists play behaviour?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A Play may provide relief from their work.", "correct": true}, {"option": "B Scientists sometimes spend time as teachers.", "correct": false}, {"option": "C The age of scientists predisposes them to play.", "correct": true}, {"option": "D Scientists get ideas from children''s questions", "correct": false}, {"option": "E Scientists are secretive about their work.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>Đáp án: A và C<br />\nDẫn chứng: (Đoạn H) “The psychologist’s answer might be that scientists tend to play because science presents them with too much seriousness [A – relief from their work]… Another possibility might be that scientists like to play because they tend to be very young [C – age].”</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b4e4afa3-3643-4f2a-b2c5-65f8302f3a6f', 'ee48504d-888a-4678-81eb-73b91aa6d874', 'matching', 'Questions 11–16', NULL, '<p>What information does the tour guide give about each of the following products?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>SIX </strong>correct letters, <strong>A-l</strong>, next to questions 11-16.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Products</strong></p>\r\n<p>hand cream {G popular overseas}</p>\r\n<p>jam {B expensive}</p>\r\n<p>soaps {A pure}</p>\r\n<p>candles {D best value for money}</p>\r\n<p>ice cream {H prize-winning}</p>\r\n<p>shampoo {F made in the village}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A pure"}, {"optionText": "B expensive"}, {"optionText": "C perfumed"}, {"optionText": "D best value for money"}, {"optionText": "E imported"}, {"optionText": "F made in the village"}, {"optionText": "G popular overseas"}, {"optionText": "H prize-winning"}, {"optionText": "I coloured"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a tour guide talking to a group of visitors about a farmers and growers market in a small New Zealand village. First you have some time to look at questions 11 to sixteen. Now listen carefully and answer questions 11 to sixteen.</p>\n<p><strong>Tour Guide (Helen):</strong> Welcome everyone to this farmers and growers market in the quiet village of Havelock North. My name is Helen and I’m your guide for the morning. Before I let you go off and explore, I’ll just tell you a few things first, which will help you know both what sort of products you will find here—there’s everything from fresh produce to handcrafts—and then how to find your way around.</p>\n<p>Right, so what do people sell here? Well, for a start, there’s some very nice <strong>hand cream</strong> from the Far North, which is always a top seller <strong>(11) abroad (G)</strong>. Those of you visitors who come from other countries may like to take it back home with you as presents because the packaging is branded ‘New Zealand’ and has pretty pictures on it of our native flowers.</p>\n<p>Now, there’s also some very tasty <strong>jam</strong> available, although because it’s made from blueberries, this product is quite <strong>(12) dear (B)</strong>, so you’ll have to spend a little more than usual. Still very delicious though!</p>\n<p>And for those of you who like your bath products gentle and suitable for sensitive skin, there are some non-allergenic <strong>soaps</strong> here. Not perfumed or coloured, just simple soap through and through, made by hand the old fashioned way with nothing artificial added <strong>(13) (A)</strong>.</p>\n<p>Ah, now there are the <strong>candles</strong> for sale at a very reasonable price. They probably represent the <strong>(14) top buy (D)</strong> if you want your dollar to stretch as far as possible. They’re just the colour of wax, so that’s not too exciting, but they do come in all different sizes to suit different purposes.</p>\n<p>Um, just a couple more items for me to tell you about. There’s great flavoured <strong>ice cream</strong> on offer. In fact, it’s so good that it’s classified export grade and was awarded the <strong>(15) gold medal (H)</strong> at this year’s food fair. You should try some!</p>\n<p>And finally, we’ve got <strong>shampoo</strong> which comes in cute little blue, green, and red bottles for three different hair types. The best thing about this product is that it’s produced right here in Havelock North <strong>(16) Village (F)</strong> by a farmer’s wife who started her own company.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the talk, you have some time to look at questions 17 to twenty. Now listen and answer questions 17 to twenty.</p>\n<p><strong>Tour Guide (Helen):</strong> Right, so that’s given you an idea of the sorts of products which are on sale at this market. Now let’s just give you a quick rundown on where to find everything, then I’ll let you go for a walk around to do your shopping.</p>\n<p>As you enter the market through the gate here in front of us, at the bottom of the map you’ve been given, you’ll see immediately that the farmers have set up their stalls out in a square in the middle of the Vineyard.</p>\n<p>I know a few of you are interested in buying <strong>(17) wooden</strong> handicrafts, so just to let you know that the stall is located on the far side of the walking track <strong>opposite the entrance (B)</strong>. There are some lovely toys for sale there and also hand-carved wooden platters and bowls.</p>\n<p>Now, the first one you’d see to your left after entering, tucked away there by the gate, is the <strong>(18) China</strong> Store <strong>(H)</strong> where there’s an interesting display of old, second-hand or antique teacups and saucers.</p>\n<p>What else? Oh, yes, the <strong>(19) Wool</strong> Shop. For those of you who are wanting to take home a New Zealand sheepskin rug or a woolly Jersey for the winter, can be found on your immediate <strong>right after you’ve gone in the entrance (E)</strong>. There are some nice scarves and hats there too.</p>\n<p>Now after all this shopping, you’ll be needing a <strong>(20) drink</strong> and something to eat, so go into the circular stand in the middle and you’ll find a stall selling local wine, fruit juices and cordials, and that’s the one at the centre <strong>top, furthest away from the main gate (G)</strong>. And also a store with lots of snack food to keep you going.</p>\n<p>Well, that’s all for me folks, now enjoy the market.</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of part 2. You now have 30 seconds to check your answers to part two.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('60c56072-581e-4e79-8865-24db7c7d6274', 'ee48504d-888a-4678-81eb-73b91aa6d874', 'matrix', 'Questions 17–20', NULL, '<p>Label the map below.</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A-H</strong></p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="data:image/png;base64," width="580" height="419" loading="lazy"></p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Wood", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "China", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "Wool", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Drinks", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3966a011-1c28-4cb9-a331-eb80c8c17d7d', 'cf209a08-6d70-42b9-99aa-6a6a1b3025d3', 'fillup', 'Question 1 - 10', '<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text ">
<div class="">
<p class="s-component-content s-font-body">Complete the table below.</p>
<p class="s-component-content s-font-body">Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer</p>
<p class="s-component-content s-font-body"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Rented Properties Information About a House</strong></span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body"> </div>
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body"><strong>Available date</strong> {5 May|5th May|May 5|May 5th}</div>
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body"> </div>
<p><strong>Prices</strong>:</p>
<p>• Rent : $ {1700} per month</p>
<p>• Desposlt: $1500</p>
<p>• {credit check|credit cheque} :$15</p>
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<p><strong>Facilities</strong>:</p>
<p>• 3 bedroom and 2 bathrooms</p>
<p>• A remodelled {kitchen|shared kitchen} .</p>
<p>• No {dishwasher}.</p>
<p>• A {garage} with a work area</p>
<p><strong>Utilities</strong></p>
<p>• The landlord will provide landscaping service, but the tenants must {water} the grass</p>
<p>• The tenants should pay $15 for trasing and {recycling} Service.</p>
<p>• The tenants should pay for electricity water and gas bills.</p>
<p><strong>Other information</strong></p>
<p>• There is no central air conditions, but there is a {window} Conditioning unit.</p>
<p>• Name of landlord: Sam {Dressler} .</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1: HOUSE RENTAL ENQUIRY</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> Hello?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> Oh, hello. I wanted to enquire about the house you’re going to let out. Is it still available?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> Yes. May I ask where you heard about it? Was it in an advert?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> Right, it was.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> OK. What do you want to know?</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_d0b521f4c47044ad-40\" data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> <span class=\"citation-137 citation-end-137\">Well, I’m going to share the house with two friends. We’ve been staying on campus, but we’re going to graduate, so we need to find a house as soon as possible anyway. Could you tell me the exact date when you can move in?</span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> Well, the contract with my current tenant is due next week on May the 3rd, and I need a day to clean and check the things in the house. So I think the house will be ready on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"188\">(1) 5th of May</strong>. Is that okay?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> Yes, that will be fine. And what we’re most concerned about is the rent. We’d like something around $500 a month for each of us, but we could go up to $600 if we have to, but we can’t go beyond that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> You are lucky. The rent will be <strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">(2) 1700</strong> dollars in total, which is within your budget. You’ll need to pay monthly to me by cash or credit card, I don’t mind. And you’ll have to pay me 1500 dollars as a deposit before you move in. Deposit is as insurance in case you break something.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> Okay, that’s reasonable.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> Oh, I nearly forgot one important thing. Is that you’ll be required to provide a <strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">(3) credit check</strong> to guarantee your ability to pay the rent every month. This will charge you $15.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> No problem. How about the facilities?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> First, there are three bedrooms combined with two bathrooms. Then there is a shared <strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">(4) kitchen</strong>, which was refurbished several months ago. By the way, do you cook yourselves?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> Yeah, we like cooking. Do we have to buy our own cookers?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> Basic facilities for cooking are available. But if you want a <strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">(5) dishwasher</strong>, I’m sorry, it needs to be added later.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> I think the basic facilities are enough for us. Is there any place we can park, as one of my friends has a private car?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> Yes, there is a <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">(6) garage</strong>, which not only provides space for your car but also has a special section where you can do some of your work. It’s very quiet for you to concentrate.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> It sounds so special.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"21\" />\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> There are some other utilities I have to tell you. There is a garden in front of the house, in which you will find some interesting plants and beautiful flowers.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> Do we have to take care of these plants and flowers?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> Well, you don’t have to worry about that. There will be a professional gardener to do the landscaping in the garden regularly. But you do need to help <strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">(7) water</strong> the grass once a week. Is it a problem for you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> Of course not, we’d like to do that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> Another thing is in this district, every household is arranged with a cleaner responsible for cleaning up the rubbish and <strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">(8) recycling</strong>. But this service will cost you $15 every month.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> What other bills do we have to pay?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> Bills for electricity, water and gas will also be covered by yourselves.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> OK, one more question. Is air conditioning available in the house?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> If you mean central air conditioning, I’m afraid there isn’t at the moment. But each room has a conditioning unit which is installed on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"150\">(9) window</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> That will be fine anyway. I think it’s a good place to live in. Can we go and see the house, please?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> Yes, of course. May I have your name and phone number?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> Yes, I’m Sam <strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"18\">(10) Dressler</strong>. That’s S-A-M, D-R-E-double S-L-E-R.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> Okay, Sam Dressler, I’ve got that down. And my phone number is 6 7 5 3 4 5 7 1.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Sam:</strong> Thank you very much. I’ll contact you after discussing it with my two friends.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Landlord:</strong> No problem. Bye bye.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7b1cfe6d-9421-4aa8-b3e9-811a42bdfd42', 'e40608b2-002e-4803-830c-c7a04c2ace26', 'matching', 'Questions 11–15', NULL, '<p data-start="122" data-end="217">Complete the flow-chart below.<br data-start="152" data-end="155">Choose <strong>FIVE </strong>correct answers, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>I</strong></p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"219\" data-end=\"244\">How to use City Cycle</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"246\" data-end=\"297\">Subscribe to the service online to receive a card</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"302\">🡇</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"304\" data-end=\"353\">At the station, log on at the computer terminal</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"302\">🡇</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"360\" data-end=\"400\">Select a bike by using the {screen}</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"302\">🡇</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"407\" data-end=\"470\">Release the bike by using the {button} of your chosen bike</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"302\">🡇</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"477\" data-end=\"541\">Remove the bike from the {rack}<br data-start=\"513\" data-end=\"516\">(You have ten seconds.)</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"302\">🡇</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"548\" data-end=\"601\">Make sure you have a {helmet} before setting off</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"299\" data-end=\"302\">🡇</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"608\" data-end=\"745\">At the end of your journey, return the bike to a station and secure in place</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"608\" data-end=\"745\">(A {light} will tell you the bike is locked correctly)</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "button"}, {"optionText": "website"}, {"optionText": "helmet"}, {"optionText": "light"}, {"optionText": "locker"}, {"optionText": "password"}, {"optionText": "rack"}, {"optionText": "screen"}, {"optionText": "sound"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 2: BICYCLE INITIATIVES</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Speaker:</strong> Thank you for all coming to today’s information session on bicycle use in the inner city.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">I’ll start by telling you about the City Council’s new bicycle hire scheme, which is called City Cycle. We want to provide people who don’t own a bike a convenient way to get around the inner city.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Now to use City Cycle, first you need to subscribe to the service, and you can do that online. Just go to the city council website and follow the prompts and you’ll be sent a card.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Once you’ve done that you can unlock one of our bikes from any station in the inner city area. Just go to the station and log on at the computer terminal.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">You’ll be shown a diagram of the bikes that are currently available at the station, so you just choose the one you want by touching the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">(11) screen [H]</strong>. You don’t need a password or anything.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">Once you’ve chosen your bike, you can then go to where the bikes are stored and push the release <strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">(12) button [A]</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">After you do that, you have about 10 seconds to take the bike out of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">(13) rack [G]</strong>. You can now start your bike ride.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">Further down the track, we’re thinking about adding lockers for bags if the scheme is popular. Oh, at this point can I just clarify something that a few people have been asking, and that is do I have to wear a <strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"210\">(14) helmet [C]</strong>?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">Well the answer is yes, you do. That’s a requirement by law in this state, so don’t forget to wear one at all times when riding.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">Now at the end of your trip, just come back to one of the city cycle stations and wheel the bike into the bike rack. It’s important to make sure that the bike is properly secured because you could be held liable if it goes missing.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">The green <strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"10\">(15) light [D]</strong> on the rack will confirm that it has been locked into place. So we hope that with such a simple scheme will have many users.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"14\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">BICYCLE CENTRE PLAN</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Speaker:</strong> Let’s turn to another initiative: the layout of the new council bicycle centre, which will be opening next week.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">This is for people who already own a bike. We wanted to provide a place for cyclists to store their bikes, then change before going on to work. Can you all see the plan?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\">If you look at the bottom towards the right-hand corner, you’ll see where the cyclists enter the centre. People want more than just a place to park their bikes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\">That’s why you’ll see a <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">(16) coffee cart [E]</strong>. That’s it there, between the reception desk and the vending machines. I’m sure it’ll be very popular with commuters first thing in the morning.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\">Now of course, some of our cyclists have very expensive bikes, so we’ll have a totally secure place for them to park. That’s it in the top right-hand corner.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\">Now there’s another special service for the cyclists that I’d like to show you. Look back at the entry on the map. Just to the left of reception, on the Donovan Street side of the building, you’ll see quite a large room.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\">That’s the <strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">(17) workshop [F]</strong> where cyclists will be able to leave their bikes for repairs while they are at work.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\">We’ve put a lot of thought into the facilities of the centre. If you have any valuables with you, you can leave these in our <strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">(18) lockers [A]</strong>. The locker room is in the top left-hand corner of your plan, so you can store your bag or wallet there before you head off for a shower.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\">We’ve installed 10 state-of-the-art power <strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">(19) showers [H]</strong>. They are located in this room here, to the left of the hair dryers and just near the exit.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\">There’s also a water cooler available so you can grab a drink, and then pick up a <strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">(20) towel [B]</strong> next to the water cooler there.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1d60401b-b7a8-421f-afd1-0e0f09ecaa47', 'f2f1038d-49ab-4540-9d38-ad109702ada4', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–10', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Horseback- trip</strong></span></p>
<p>Length of trip: two days</p>
<p>Best month to go: September</p>
<p>Might see large numbers of {birds}</p>
<p>Type of accommodation: a {tent}</p>
<p><strong>Day one</strong></p>
<p>Final destination: {mountains}</p>
<p>Evening activity: chance to have a {swim}</p>
<p><strong>Day two</strong></p>
<p>Explore the valley and have lunch by a {waterfall}</p>
<p>Afternoon trip to a {cave}</p>
<p><strong>Tips for the holiday</strong></p>
<p>· unsuitable if you have {back} problems</p>
<p>· rocky paths so take {walking boots}</p>
<p><strong>Booking details</strong></p>
<p>Book online to get a {discount}</p>
<p>Inform your {insurance} company about the type of holiday booked</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 1</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jenny:</strong> hi Greg great to see you and thanks for emailing me with the details of the horseback riding trip you went on. I looked at the website and it looks great.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Greg:</strong> yeah I went on the 2 day mini break. Is that what you’re thinking about?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jenny:</strong> yes that’s the one. Do you think they’d have places now in July or will it be full?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Greg:</strong> if you can hang on till September, that’s when I went and it was a really great time to go. It’s not so hot for a start.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jenny:</strong> that’d suit me better anyway.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Greg:</strong> and also at one point when we stopped for a picnic, I was lying in a field looking up and saw a huge flock of <strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">(1) birds</strong>. They were obviously migrating. That’s another reason why it’s a good time to go.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jenny:</strong> oh great.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Greg:</strong> oh and another thing. You don’t stay in a hotel, you stay in a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">(2) tent</strong></span>, so you don’t have to come back to town in the evening.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jenny:</strong> I’m up for that. So where do you go on the first day?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Greg:</strong> through some amazing wooded valleys full of chestnut and beech trees. But that’s just the morning. Where you’re really heading for is the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">(3) mountains</strong></span>, and when you set out, you can only see them in the far distance. You don’t actually get there until sunset.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jenny:</strong> is it hard work riding all day?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Greg:</strong> no the pace is easy, and there are plenty of breaks built in for picnics and even a snooze. But on that first evening, when you’ve been riding all day, you get the opportunity to go for a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"194\">(4) swim</strong></span> and you’ll really enjoy that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jenny:</strong> so relaxing. And what’s on day 2? You said something about the national park?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Greg:</strong> no, day two you go up this incredible valley. At the end of it there’s a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">(5) waterfall</strong></span>. It’s an amazing place to stop for lunch. We even spotted an eagle while we were sitting there. And in the afternoon there’s a trip that goes to a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"240\">(6) cave</strong></span>. You can even ride into it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jenny:</strong> wow that sounds great I can’t wait.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"18\" />\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Greg:</strong> okay so what are your tips for horseback riding weekend?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jenny:</strong> well I had a sore knee before I went and I was pretty worried about that. It was okay actually, but what you’ve got to watch for is that you don’t have any trouble with your <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"181\">(7) back</strong></span>. Riding can really aggravate that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jenny:</strong> no problem there. And comfortable clothes I guess?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Greg:</strong> yeah, but another thing I hadn’t realized is that you actually walk the horses down some pretty steep and uneven paths, so make sure you have <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">(8) walking boots</strong></span>, not just normal riding boots. And even if you’re going in the autumn, make sure you don’t get sunburnt. Even if it looks cloudy take sunscreen, lots of it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jenny:</strong> I think you’ve convinced me to sign up. When I was looking at the website, I saw that if I register online, I can get a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">(9) discount</strong></span>. Did you do that or go through a travel agency?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Greg:</strong> I registered online of course. I just have to let my boss know when I want to take time off. And then the other important thing I read was that you have to make sure that your <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"182\">(10) insurance</strong> </span>company know that you’re going on an adventure trip to make sure that you’re covered in case anything happens. I’m sure it won’t, but better be safe than sorry.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a1c5e100-64e9-4c73-8292-5fd012e62246', 'dfe8748e-12ba-45d3-b622-91e5f3d4233d', 'checkbox', 'Questions 29 and 30', '', '<p data-start="1940" data-end="1968">Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>E</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="1970" data-end="2067">Which <strong>TWO </strong>things do Mark and Stella suggest doing with regard to note-taking on a field trip?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A. Ensure that terminology is correctly used in the notes"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "B. Check your notes every evening"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C. Be highly selective in what you write down"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D. Have only one member of a team to write notes"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "E. Keep your notes in an organised fashion"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('427aac3d-9d5d-4a0b-ab4a-041c217de8be', '1bf722d0-0787-401d-b345-198af6f4bb80', 'fillup', 'Questions 7–10', '<p data-path-to-node="11">Complete the table below.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="12">Write <strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="6">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9592%; height: 2px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 2px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 33.3478%;"><col style="width: 33.3478%;"><col style="width: 33.3478%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="3"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>A typical 45-minute guitar lesson</strong></span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;"><strong>Time</strong></td>
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;"><strong>Activity</strong></td>
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;"><strong><span data-path-to-node="14,0,2,0">Notes</span></strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">5 minutes</td>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">tuning guitars</td>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p data-path-to-node="14,1,2,0">using an app or by {ear}</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">10 minutes</td>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">strumming chords using our thumbs</td>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p data-path-to-node="14,2,2,0">keeping time while the teacher is {clapping}</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">15 minutes</td>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;"><span data-path-to-node="14,3,1,0">playing songs</span></td>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p data-path-to-node="14,3,2,0">often listening to a {recording} of a song</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">10 minutes</td>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">playing single notes and simple tunes</td>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p data-path-to-node="14,4,2,0">playing together, then {alone}</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">5 minutes</td>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;"><span data-path-to-node="14,5,1,0">noting things to practise at home</span></td>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;"> </td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p data-path-to-node="12"> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d193574a-a804-40b8-af9b-791447a0b7b3', '4207ab5a-bffb-4788-ae89-6367d6c8a524', 'radio', 'Questions 1-5', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information <strong>NOT</strong> <strong>GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The early Spanish called potato as the Incan name ''Chuño''."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The purpose of Spanish coming to Peru was to find potatoes."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Spanish believed that the potato had the same nutrients as other vegetables."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Peasants at that time did not like to eat potatoes because they were ugly,"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The popularity of potatoes in the UK was due to food shortages during the war."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1. The early Spanish called potato as the Incan name ‘Chuño’.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 2) “Early Spanish chroniclers who misused the Indian word </span><strong class=\"\">batata</strong><span class=\"\"> (sweet potato) as the name for the potato noted the importance of the tuber to the Incan Empire.</span><span class=\"\"> The Incas had learned to preserve the potato…</span><span class=\"\"> into a substance called </span><strong class=\"\">Chuño</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Người Tây Ban Nha dùng nhầm từ </span><strong class=\"\">“batata”</strong><span class=\"\"> (khoai lang) để gọi củ khoai tây,</span><span class=\"\"> chứ không phải dùng từ “Chuño” (tên món khoai tây nghiền bảo quản của người Inca).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>2. The purpose of Spanish coming to Peru was to find potatoes.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 3) “The Spanish conquistadors first encountered the potato when they arrived in Peru in 1532 </span><strong class=\"\">in search of gold</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Mục đích chính của người Tây Ban Nha là tìm kiếm </span><strong class=\"\">vàng</strong><span class=\"\"> (gold),</span><span class=\"\"> không phải khoai tây.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>3. The Spanish believed that the potato had the same nutrients as other vegetables.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 3) “…</span><span class=\"\">they did gradually begin to use potatoes as </span><strong class=\"\">basic rations</strong><span class=\"\"> aboard their ships.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Văn bản chỉ nói người Tây Ban Nha dùng khoai tây làm khẩu phần cơ bản,</span> <strong class=\"\">không đề cập</strong><span class=\"\"> đến niềm tin của họ về giá trị dinh dưỡng của khoai tây so với các loại rau củ khác.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>4. Peasants at that time did not like to eat potatoes because they were ugly.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 4) “Even peasants refused to eat from a plant that produced </span><strong class=\"\">ugly, misshapen tubers</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Người nông dân từ chối ăn khoai tây vì chúng xấu xí và méo mó (ugly,</span><span class=\"\"> misshapen tubers).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>5. The popularity of potatoes in the UK was due to food shortages during the war.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 5) “Potatoes did not become a staple until,</span><span class=\"\"> during the </span><strong class=\"\">food shortages associated with the Revolutionary Wars</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> the English government began to officially encourage potato cultivation.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Khoai tây trở thành lương thực chính ở Anh trong thời kỳ </span><strong class=\"\">thiếu lương thực liên quan đến chiến tranh</strong><span class=\"\">.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7307abae-ef7f-48fe-bb7a-90351d89e09d', '42e8e397-2d6e-44d9-9bf6-267a5e1f3aaa', 'radio', 'Questions 11-14', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B or C:</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": " A. in the sports ground.  "}, {"content": "B. by the river.  "}, {"content": "C. in the shopping centre."}], "question": "On the day of the race the speaker recommends parking:"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. the shirt or singlet.  "}, {"content": "B. a shoe.  "}, {"content": "C. the wristband."}], "question": "The timing chip should be attached to:    "}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. yellow.  "}, {"content": "B. red.  "}, {"content": "C. purple."}], "question": "Which group will run first?    "}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. giving first aid."}, {"content": "B. handing out water. "}, {"content": "C. starting the race."}], "question": "The race organisers still need to find volunteers to help with:       "}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a coordinator talking to volunteer helpers before a race involving a large number of people. First you have some time to look at questions 11 to 14 on page three. Now listen carefully and answer questions 11 to fourteen.</p>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Thank you for all volunteering to help us with the Bridge to Brisbane fun run. The purpose of this meeting is to give you some information about your duties on race day. Some of you are asking about where you can park on the day. Unfortunately, some of the usual places down by the river for example, will be out of bounds because we’ll need extra space for emergency vehicles. Probably the best option is the Jack Gray Sports field in Barker Street <strong>(11) (A)</strong>. Although the closest parking lot is the Metro Shopping Complex, I would advise you not to park there as they tend to tow away people who aren’t customers.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Cảm ơn tất cả các bạn đã tình nguyện giúp chúng tôi trong sự kiện chạy vui “Bridge to Brisbane”. Mục đích của cuộc họp này là cung cấp cho các bạn một số thông tin về nhiệm vụ của mình vào ngày đua. Một số bạn hỏi về nơi đỗ xe trong ngày. Thật không may, một số địa điểm quen thuộc như ven sông sẽ bị cấm vì chúng tôi cần thêm không gian cho xe cấp cứu. Lựa chọn tốt nhất có lẽ là <strong>(11) Sân vận động Jack Gray</strong> ở phố Barker <strong>(A)</strong>. Mặc dù bãi đậu xe gần nhất là Khu phức hợp mua sắm Metro, tôi khuyên các bạn không nên đỗ xe ở đó vì họ có xu hướng kéo xe đi nếu không phải là khách hàng.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> At the start line, most of you will be checking that runners have the necessary gear, especially their electronic timing chip, the race number and the identity wristband. Make sure that the number is attached to the front of the running shirt or singlet, not the back. The timing chip which records the runner’s time needs to be clipped onto <strong>(12) one of their shoes (B)</strong>, and check that they are wearing their wristband.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Tại vạch xuất phát, hầu hết các bạn sẽ kiểm tra xem các vận động viên có đầy đủ thiết bị cần thiết hay không, đặc biệt là chip định giờ điện tử, số hiệu cuộc đua và vòng đeo tay nhận dạng. Hãy đảm bảo số hiệu được gắn ở phía trước áo chạy hoặc áo ba lỗ, không phải phía sau. Chip định giờ ghi lại thời gian của vận động viên cần được kẹp vào <strong>(12) một trong những chiếc giày của họ (B)</strong>, và kiểm tra xem họ có đang đeo vòng đeo tay nhận dạng không.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Some of you will be responsible for organizing the starting groups. It’s very important that runners start in a particular order. There is a system of color codes. The red group are walkers and people with baby strollers. The purple group are runners that expect to finish in at less than one hour, and the <strong>(13) yellow group (A)</strong> are our Elite athletes. We’d like them to start the race, and we’d like the other groups to follow after that, with the red group and the strollers at the very back. This is for their own safety.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Một số bạn sẽ chịu trách nhiệm tổ chức các nhóm xuất phát. Rất quan trọng để các vận động viên bắt đầu theo một thứ tự cụ thể. Có một hệ thống mã màu. Nhóm màu đỏ là những người đi bộ và những người có xe đẩy em bé. Nhóm màu tím là những vận động viên dự kiến hoàn thành dưới một giờ, và <strong>(13) nhóm màu vàng (A)</strong> là các vận động viên ưu tú của chúng ta. Chúng tôi muốn họ bắt đầu cuộc đua, và chúng tôi muốn các nhóm khác theo sau, với nhóm màu đỏ và xe đẩy ở phía sau cùng. Điều này là vì sự an toàn của chính họ.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Now we are still short on volunteers for the race day, so if you have any friends or family members who might be interested, please let us know. We’re probably okay for people to help with the start, but we’ll still desperately need volunteers along the race course to <strong>(14) distribute water bottles to the runners (B)</strong>. A few of you have offered to help with First Aid, but the good people of Saint John’s Ambulance have donated their services, so that won’t be necessary.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Hiện tại chúng tôi vẫn còn thiếu tình nguyện viên cho ngày đua, vì vậy nếu bạn có bất kỳ bạn bè hoặc thành viên gia đình nào quan tâm, vui lòng cho chúng tôi biết. Chúng tôi có lẽ ổn về nhân lực giúp đỡ ở vạch xuất phát, nhưng chúng tôi vẫn cần tình nguyện viên dọc theo đường đua để <strong>(14) phân phát chai nước cho các vận động viên (B)</strong>. Một vài bạn đã đề nghị giúp đỡ Sơ cứu, nhưng những người tốt của xe cứu thương Saint John đã tặng dịch vụ của họ, vì vậy điều đó sẽ không cần thiết.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the talk, you have some time to look at questions fifteen to twenty on page four. Now listen and answer questions fifteen to twenty.</p>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Now I’ll show you the layout of the Race Village, which is where the race ends. Can you all see the map? If you look at the bottom right hand side, you’ll see where the runners enter the Village next to the corporate catering section. As you continue along the course, you’ll see the <strong>(15) stage (F)</strong> on your right. That’s where the winners will receive their medals. Now can you all see the finish line near the center? After they finish the race, the runners can take one of two paths, it doesn’t matter which one, to get their finishers T shirts from the <strong>(16) T-shirt stand (A)</strong> at the end of those paths.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Bây giờ tôi sẽ chỉ cho các bạn bố cục của Làng Đua (Race Village), nơi cuộc đua kết thúc. Tất cả các bạn có thấy bản đồ không? Nếu bạn nhìn vào phía dưới bên phải, bạn sẽ thấy nơi các vận động viên vào Làng, bên cạnh khu vực phục vụ ăn uống của công ty. Khi bạn tiếp tục dọc theo đường đua, bạn sẽ thấy <strong>(15) sân khấu (F)</strong> ở bên phải của mình. Đó là nơi những người chiến thắng sẽ nhận huy chương. Bây giờ tất cả các bạn có thể thấy vạch đích gần trung tâm không? Sau khi hoàn thành cuộc đua, các vận động viên có thể đi một trong hai con đường, không quan trọng là con đường nào, để nhận áo T-shirt dành cho người hoàn thành từ <strong>(16) quầy áo T-shirt (A)</strong> ở cuối những con đường đó.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Many of you will be stationed there at the end of the race. After they finish, the runners will also want their belongings, and all bags are kept in the <strong>(17) bag collection area (B)</strong> on Bowen Road. It’s quite close to the exit in the top left hand corner of your map.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Nhiều bạn sẽ được bố trí ở đó vào cuối cuộc đua. Sau khi hoàn thành, các vận động viên cũng sẽ muốn lấy đồ đạc của họ, và tất cả túi xách được giữ ở <strong>(17) khu vực nhận túi (B)</strong> trên Đường Bowen. Nó khá gần lối ra ở góc trên bên trái của bản đồ của bạn.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Now some of you will have an important role working in the <strong>(18) information centre (H)</strong>. That’s the building in the center of the map, not far from the finish line, it’s just below it on your map. And one other thing, can you all please remind the runners to enter in the prize draw for the new car. The entry box is between the shade tents and the corporate catering buildings <strong>(19) (G)</strong>.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Bây giờ một số bạn sẽ có vai trò quan trọng làm việc tại <strong>(18) Trung tâm thông tin (H)</strong>. Đó là tòa nhà ở trung tâm bản đồ, không xa vạch đích, nó nằm ngay bên dưới trên bản đồ của bạn. Và một điều nữa, các bạn hãy nhắc nhở các vận động viên tham gia rút thăm trúng thưởng xe ô tô mới. Hộp đăng ký nằm giữa các lều che nắng và khu vực phục vụ ăn uống của công ty <strong>(19) (G)</strong>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Okay, let’s see now what else do I need to point out. Ah yes, the runners are always thirsty, and the main <strong>(20) water station (I)</strong> in the Village is just beside the third exit through to Gregory Terrace. Can you see it there, to the left of the corporate catering area? So everyone please direct the race finishers there to get their free bottle water <strong>(20) (I)</strong>.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> Được rồi, bây giờ xem tôi cần chỉ ra điều gì nữa. À vâng, các vận động viên luôn khát, và <strong>(20) trạm nước (I)</strong> chính trong Làng nằm ngay bên cạnh lối ra thứ ba dẫn ra Sân thượng Gregory. Các bạn có thấy nó ở đó không, bên trái khu vực phục vụ ăn uống của công ty? Vì vậy, mọi người hãy hướng dẫn những người hoàn thành cuộc đua đến đó để lấy chai nước miễn phí của họ <strong>(20) (I)</strong>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of section two. You now have half a minute to check your answers.</p>\n"}]', 0);
SET session_replication_role = DEFAULT;
